## Conversation
User asked (in this session) to first audit the weave package (excl. trace_server)
for separation-of-concerns/modularity/testability via a fan-out of subagents, then
to "show what the integration refactor and op system refactors would look like" and
"make a stacked PR for those 2 changes." This is branch 1 of the stack (op system);
branch 2 (integrations) is stacked on top.

The audit's finding F-B1 was: op.py has 4 near-identical execution paths whose
finish() closure is copy-pasted verbatim 4x (lines 506-535, 635-664, 773-802,
995-1024 on master), and the logic can't be unit-tested without a full op run.
This commit addresses exactly that finding (the safest, highest-value slice). The
larger F-B2 "OpState dataclass" consolidation was deliberately deferred (39+ files
read op.* attributes directly; too invasive for one PR).

